\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 \'a0brings up the help overlay. The seed button randomizes, format presets change the canvas aspect ratio, and actions like pin and save trigger toast notifications.\cb1 \
\cb3 For the canvas placeholder, I'm rendering a subtle particle flow field that shifts color with the theme accent\'97varying a parameter per module so switching between them feels dynamic. If the user prefers reduced motion, I'll show a static frame instead.\cb1 \
\cb3 Building this out as a single HTML artifact now, keeping the CSS clean and mobile-responsive so the rail collapses and the panel adapts gracefully on smaller screens.\cb1 \
\cb3 For typography, I'm loading Archivo at multiple weights plus JetBrains Mono for code, though I might streamline the font requests to avoid bloat.\cb1 \
\cb3 Now I'm drafting the full HTML structure. I'll skip loading messages since this is a file artifact, and I'm being disciplined with color\'97using accent colors only for active modules, slider fills, focus states, the recording indicator, theme names, and active pins, keeping everything else neutral grey.\cb1 \
\cb3 I'm adding a subtle film grain texture using SVG noise...\cb1 \
\cb3 For the canvas animation, I'm building a lightweight particle flow system with around 600 particles moving through a noise field using additive blending with low alpha trails, recolored by the accent. The flow field itself will use a cheap layered sine-based approach for the angle calculations rather than full Perlin noise to keep it performant, and I'll respect reduced motion by rendering a single static frame instead.\cb1 \
